{"comments":"XYZ - CIE 1931 XYZ color space (device-independent).\n\n**FOUNDATION OF COLOR SCIENCE:**\nXYZ is THE fundamental color space in professional color management.\nCreated by the International Commission on Illumination (CIE) in 1931,\nit's based on how human cone cells actually respond to light.\n\n**Why XYZ exists:**\nRGB is device-dependent - same RGB values look different on different screens.\nXYZ is device-independent - same XYZ values produce the same perceived color\non any calibrated device. This is why every ICC color profile uses XYZ.\n\n**Components (Tristimulus values):**\n- **X**: Roughly corresponds to red-green (0.0-0.95047 for D65 white)\n- **Y**: Luminance/brightness (0.0-1.0, where 1.0 = perfect white)\n- **Z**: Roughly corresponds to blue-yellow (0.0-1.08883 for D65 white)\n\n**White point:**\nThis module uses D65 illuminant (standard for sRGB displays):\n- X = 0.95047\n- Y = 1.00000\n- Z = 1.08883\n\n**The conversion bridge:**\nYou CANNOT convert RGB ↔ LAB directly. The path is:\n```\nRGB → XYZ → LAB → LCH\nLCH → LAB → XYZ → RGB\n```\n\n**Use cases:**\n- ICC color profile conversions\n- Cross-device color matching\n- Professional color management\n- Scientific color measurements\n- Accurate color space transformations\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"XYZ color - CIE 1931 device-independent color space\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["x",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","XYZ"],"XComponent"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["y",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","XYZ"],"YComponent"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["z",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","XYZ"],"ZComponent"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[139,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/XYZ.purs","start":[135,1]},"title":"XYZ"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","XYZ"],"XComponent"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[74,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/XYZ.purs","start":[74,1]},"title":"eqXComponent"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","XYZ"],"XComponent"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[75,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/XYZ.purs","start":[75,1]},"title":"ordXComponent"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Color","XYZ"],"XComponent"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[78,39],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/XYZ.purs","start":[77,1]},"title":"showXComponent"}],"comments":"X component (tristimulus value): 0.0-0.95047 (D65 white)\nRoughly corresponds to red-green axis\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[72,39],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Color/XYZ.purs","start":[72,1]},"title":"XComponent"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[]